rComments: Denis is very caring about his student's education and wellbeing. He is engaging and well-versed, while still being open to different ideas and perspectives from diverse disciplines. He provides detailed feedback on written work and creates an environment conducive to learning in lectures. Highly recommended!
Denis is a fantastic guy. As brilliant as he is modest and approachable. I really enjoyed learning from him and look froward to the opportunity to take another clas with him should the chance arise.
teacherRatingTags: ['Participation matters', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Outstanding. Extremely knowledgeable, approachable, and witty. Displays empathy for students juggling too many things at once. Balances workload, seeks input from class re: deadlines, always available via e-mail or will arrange appointment at his office. Very fiar with grades. A benchmark for all other professors to emulate.
He's an easy teacher to get a long with and it's really easy to talk to him if you have a problem with something.

One great professor--organized, articulate, intelligent, funny, sincere, and respectful of students. Made classroom experience the opposite of boring for students willing to engage with the material in a deeper level. Uninterested students looking for a typical philosophy class will not appreciate this professor.
